description: It took almost 500 days for Belgium to agree a government, but it does not include the top two parties.
title: Why Belgian struggle for identity could tear country apart
title_page: Why Belgian struggle for identity could tear country apart - BBC News
maintext: The immediate focus for his party's anger now is the fallout from the 2019 parliamentary elections, in which his party came first and the far-right Vlaams Belang movement second, but do not feature in the new government.
